dismissalText.commentary: Michael Hussey c Dippenaar b Pollock 56 (73b 4x4 1x6 102m) SR: 76.71

dismissalComment.html: gone!! that was a rank bad shot. Pollock bowls one just a little short, and a little too straight, Hussey pulls it away off the backfoot, cant keep it down, and finds Boeta Dippenaar at the midwicket fence - that's two wickets in two overs for Pollock - justifies Graeme Smith's move of bringing him on

dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke c de Villiers b Pollock 53 (82b 6x4 0x6 109m) SR: 64.63

dismissalComment.html: Pollock strikes!! slower delivery from Pollock, just a bit on offer, Clarke falls prey to it, drives in the air, but cant find the gap, drives to the left of AB De Villiers who's fielding at cover, he dives to his left and pulls off a fantastic catch!

commentTextItems.html: there you go! comes down the track and chips it over the man at midwicket, ball races away to the fence

commentPostTextItems.html: South Africa win by 6 wickets and they now lead the 5 match ODI series 1-0.
Man of the Match - Graeme Smith

commentTextItems.html: turned away to short fine leg, no room for a single there
2 5;driven wide of the fielder at midwicket - scores are level!
four more! short of a good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Kemp swings across, just like a Japanese fan opening up, and the ball rockets away to the fine leg fence

commentTextItems.html: bit of width outside the off stump, cut away off the back-foot to the third man region
pitched up outside the off stump and Smith drives it through the gap between mid-on and midwicket, Hussey chases it down - just eight more to get now!
short delivery down the leg side, Kemp stays back and slaps it down to fine leg for an easy single
good length delivery, driven straight to the fielder at cover
shot! short of a good length and on the stumps, nothing wrong with the delivery, Kemp just stands tall and front-foot and pulls it away to the midwicket fence - amazing shot
another fulltoss, Smith fails to time it properly and the ball goes straight to the fielder at midwicket

commentTextItems.html: fulltoss on the pads, worked away to fine leg for a single, South Africa inching closer to a memorable win here
mistimed cut and the ball rolls away towards point
flighted delivery outside the off stump, Smith gets a good stride forward and punches it away well wide of the fielder at gully
quicker delivery, drifting down the leg side and Kemp tucks it away behind square leg, easy run
driven straight to the fielder at cover
short ball outside the off stump, swing and miss

commentTextItems.html: good length delivery on the stumps, Smith dances down the track and hammers it away to the long-off fence, good clean hit - one bounce and over the rope she goes
turned wide of the fielder at midwicket
short of a good length delivery, this one nipped back in sharply, Kemp is beaten by the angle and the bounce, ball hits the upper part of the pad and rolls away behind the stumps
on middle and leg, turned away straight to the fielder at midwicket
